    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-11T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-11T23:00:00-05:00" n="448"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13322: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-12T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 12, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 12—9:45
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>136. The Central Executive Committee this morning names the following “Cabinet”
                    Ministers: <list>
                        <item>Interior, Chiang Tso-pin;</item>
                        <item>Foreign Affairs, Chang Chun;</item>
                        <item>Military Administration, Ho Ying-chin;</item>
                        <item>Navy, Chen Shao-kuan;</item>
                        <item>Finance, H. H. Kung;</item>
                        <item>Industries, Wu Ting-chang;</item>
                        <item>Communications, Ku Meng-yu;</item>
                        <item>Education, Wang Shih-chieh;</item>
                        <item>Railways, Chang Kia-ngau (Chang Kung-chuan).</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
